    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "> In error messages like `Expected transaction to be reverted with reason 'some reason', but it reverted with a custom error`, we should include the selector of the custom error.\r\n\r\nI was testing a scenario where I send Ether to a contract without receive or fallback functions, the test code expects a revert with reason 'function selector was not recognized and there's no fallback nor receive function' and it worked using Waffle. When I've upgraded to chai-matchers the test started to fail because it is reverted without a reason.",
